<p>You're better off just buying the blocks of HQ ore. To make from fine steel weapons: <br /> <br />1 fine steel weapons-----&gt; 1 small brick HQ ore <br />3 small bricks HQ ore-----&gt; 1 large brick HQ ore <br />3 large bricks HQ ore-----&gt; 1 block HQ ore <br /> <br />So, for 9 FS weapons, you end up with 1 Block of HQ ore. Just selling the FS you would have gotten 37.8pp at max charisma for 9 (4.2pp each), and thus for all your trouble are only saving 12.2 pp per Block. Since the race-specific items for the new cultural smithing recipes such as a pile of gravel, basilisk tooth, etc, are so rare, you'll likely only be making a few pieces at a time. Do yourself a favor and just by the Block for 51pp. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Thu Mar 10 09:39:32 2005 by Gladestrider</span></i></p>
